{"actual_usd":0.15572,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":161,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30661,"reply":"\"I think it was the same body, glorified — not swapped out for a different one.\" *I rest a thumb in the crease of my Bible and glance up at the clear morning light in the square.* \"That’s why the wounds still matter, and why he can say, in effect, it’s really me. But it’s also a new kind of life in that body — raised, not merely resuscitated.\"\n\n*I rub once at my jaw, thinking it through.* \"The recognition part doesn’t trouble me much. Sometimes their eyes seem restrained until the right moment; sometimes grief and shock have made them slow; and sometimes Jesus is simply doing something deeper than ordinary recognition. Same Jesus, same risen body — but now under resurrection conditions, not the old ordinary limits.\"","rolling_24h_usd":80.16802999999996,"run_id":"a75d76bf-598d-4627-b5a1-e0e9a8b0597a"}
